sentences: Stuart Leslie Braithwaite (born 10 May 1976) is a Scottish multi-instrumentalist, singer and songwriter.
He attended Strathaven Academy from 1987 to 1993.
Before playing in Mogwai, Braithwaite fronted a band called Deadcat Motorbike, who broke up in June 1995.
Formation and first years of Mogwai (1995–1996) ==
section: == Formation and first years of Mogwai (1995–1996) ==

sentences: Braithwaite met Dominic Aitchison at a Ned's Atomic Dustbin show at the Queen Margaret Union in Glasgow on 10 April 1991, and four years later, along with school friend Martin Bulloch, they formed Mogwai.
section: == Formation and first years of Mogwai (1995–1996) ==

sentences: In 2000, Braithwaite played with a band called Mighty Joe Young Trio.
In 2000 and 2002, Braithwaite performed solo acoustic shows.
In 2002, Braithwaite, Aidan Moffat and Colin "Sheepy" McPherson released an eponymously titled EP called The Sick Anchors.
In 2016 Braithwaite took part in a documentary about Glasgow music, and Chemikal Underground Records, called Lost in France.
Braithwaite married musician Elisabeth Elektra in April 2019.
